# Dhall config topology — host-local / secret-bearing / generated config; never
# included in the image. Sprint 1.49: the in-cluster container does NOT ship a
# committed or COPY-ed default Tier-0 config; it RUNs the binary
# (`prodbox config generate`) at build time to write its binary-sibling
# `prodbox.dhall` (config_doctrine.md §0, §3). So the host's local prodbox.dhall
# must never leak in, and the generated *-types.dhall schemas are regenerated by
# the binary, not shipped. Sprint 1.43: test-secrets.dhall is the SOLE
# durable-secret fixture (elevated AWS creds + the ZeroSSL ACME EAB key) and must
# never enter the build context; the now-removed test-config(.dhall/-types.dhall)
# files are gone (do not re-add them here).
prodbox-config.dhall
prodbox-config.json
prodbox-config-types.dhall
test-secrets.dhall
test-secrets-types.dhall
prodbox.dhall

